Goals:

Review the new feature implementation and identify:
duplicated logic
unnecessary complexity
poor abstractions
inconsistent patterns
potential bugs or edge cases
performance issues
security concerns
technical debt introduced by the feature

Compare the new code against the existing codebase conventions:

naming
folder/module structure
error handling
state management
API patterns
testing style

Refactor the code to:

simplify logic
reduce coupling
improve separation of concerns
remove dead code
improve testability
make future changes easier
